With the end of the compulsory lever, decreed on January 1, 2005, the Italian forces have passed to the professional army. Since then, the army sees an organic of about 93,000 soldiers. The armed forces - without the 108,000 carabinieri - have 168 thousand army units, aeronautics and marina. In practice we have more carabinieri chesoldi. In an audition to the Chamber Defense Commission, the head of statomaggiore of the army, General Pietro Serino said that: "Also inconsideration of the current situation, with the war returned to the heart of Europe, the army must aim for the finish line of at least 110,000 Men Edonne, who would also be consistent with the qualitative needs and staff of staff ". "We cannot ignore that unfortunately the war between states has returned to the Europadopo 77 years. And for the army it is a question of restoring skills that in the last years seemed to belong to the past, or to a distant future, to deign with new units dedicated to cybernetic domains e Space ", haa. According to what is explained by General Serino, "the general orientation is to return to the numbers of the original professional model, abandoned in 2012, the pressure of a difficult economic situation", or "110.000uomini and women" compared to the current 93,100. A number that would allow to "respond adequately to the complexity of the challenges to security" and to "manage the tools that technology makes available". General Serino therefore underlined the need to increase Ilnumero of officers compared to the total of the actual, up to dispose of "9,800 out of 93,100" effective, with a percentage equal to "10.5%", as well as Ilnumero of non -commissioned officers, with "a" increase of 1,900 ". The percentage of the Military Organic Distactory is 37.6%. The General stressed that the officers represent 13% of the French army, 16% of the British one and 16.8% of that hetemedes. Italy must therefore bring this share at least 10/11%.

