![](Images/Philippine Revolution Web Central/2023-02-23T93-00-00-04-00/barangay-mataragan-malibcong-abra-1024x545.png )Together on Tuesday, February 21, parents and teachers of the National Agricultural School in Barangay Mataragan, Malibcong, Abralaban were involved in the soldiers who were campaigning inside the school, due to the threat of children's security. They successfully drove the soldiers away.

Residents have complained that the entire community has always been disturbed because of the presence of soldiers in the area. They can no longer work in their lives and travel to the forests due to unstable military operations.

Meanwhile, the pressures and interrogation of militararkay agents Jerome Agaid, a farmer belonging to the Mabaca's Peaceproof Mabaca, who lived in Mataragan, Malibcong, reported. Agaid joined on February 16, 2023 with his 5-year-old fisher fisheries in Barangaygadani, Tayum, Abra, when soldiers were attacked and held.

Due to this incident and other previous military abuse of Saabra, the actions of the people have grown stronger to complain about a great event.(NPRA report)

